## Handoff Receiving Template

```
=== WINDSURF HANDOFF PACKAGE ===
Project: [repo name]
Branch: [branch name]
Handed off from: [platform] ([phase completed])
Receiving: Windsurf / Cascade ([phase beginning])

--- PROJECT CONTEXT FILE ---
[Create or update a CONTEXT.md or .windsurf/rules file with:]

## Project
[2-sentence description]

## Stack
[Language, framework, key dependencies]

## Current Task
[What this Windsurf session is for]

## Conventions
[Naming, file structure, patterns to follow]

## Acceptance Criteria
[What "done" looks like]

## Do Not Modify
[Files, directories, patterns that must not change]

--- CASCADE PROMPT ---
[Paste into Windsurf Cascade:]

You are continuing work on [project]. Current state:

Completed:
- [What exists and works]

Your task:
1. [First action — reference file paths]
2. [Second action]
3. [Third action]

Constraints:
- [Hard constraint 1]
- [Hard constraint 2]

When complete, output:
- Files changed
- Decisions made
- Any blockers
This will be used for: /handoff return from Windsurf

=== END ===
```

## Configuration Checklist
- [ ] Confirm project is open in Windsurf
- [ ] Create or update project context file before starting
- [ ] Confirm correct branch is checked out
- [ ] Use Cascade mode for multi-file tasks (not standard chat)
- [ ] Define acceptance criteria before starting — Cascade performs better with clear done-states
